    • neighboringColorCell

      public static int[][] neighboringColorCell​(Builder currentBuilder)
      the method builds and return a matrix 3*3 of integers in which each cell contains a 0 or a 1, a 0 if the correspondent cell in the board is either free or occupied by a current player's builder; a 1 if the cell is occupied by a builder of the current player's opponent. All the cell of the board examined by the method are neighboring the current builder used by the current player
      Parameters:
      currentBuilder - is the reference of the current builder used by the current player
      Returns:
      a matrix 3*3 of integers

    • neighboringSwappingCell

      public static int[][] neighboringSwappingCell​(Builder builder, AccessType target)
      the method creates a matrix 3*3 that shows in which cell there is an opponent's builder that can be swapped with the builder of current player, the cells' values of this matrix are calculated by multiplying the respective values of neighboringColorCell and neighboringStatusCell: The value of the cell will be 0 if the correspondent cell of the board is either free, occupied by the other builder of the player or the cell is inaccessible by the builder. In all the other cases the cell will have the values of the correspondent cell of neighboringStatusCell
      Parameters:
      builder - is the current player's builder, the cell where it is will be the respective centre of the returned matrix
      target - will passed to neighboringStatusCell, and its value will be OCCUPIED
      Returns:
      is the matrix of integers described above
